    "text": [
        "The Internet is now an integral part of modern life as a result of the emergence of the Fourth Industrial Revolution. Internet technology has undoubtedly revolutionized the way people communicate with one another. In my opinion, I strongly agree with this viewpoint.",
        "First of all, there is no doubt that the internet facilitates faster communication between people dispersed geographically since it facilitates faster communication between people. Before the advent of the internet, the only means of communication between people was through letters. Depending on the distance, it could take as long as a few days, or even weeks, to receive handwritten letters containing only very little information. As a result of the internet, people today have not only been able to chat within seconds or make video calls within minutes but the process of reporting has evolved into a much easier and more efficient one, whether it is for the public or private sector.",
        "Furthermore, with the advent of the internet, it is now possible to chat and make friends across the globe. Due to the emergence of social media platforms, the internet has enabled people from all around the world to communicate much more easily and conveniently than they have ever done before. In spite of cultures that may differ, people listen to each other's stories and gain a greater understanding, an enhanced sense of empathy, and a greater understanding of people and cultures from around the world, thus strengthening the bond between them.",
        "In conclusion, I believe that technological advancements and the Internet have resulted in a reduction of communication distances between people due to the increased utilization of the Internet."
